Retroperitoneal bronchogenic cyst presenting as an adrenal mass.
 Subdiaphragmatic bronchogenic cysts are rare, and those located retroperitoneally are exceptional.
 A review of the English-language literature revealed only three reported cases.
 We describe an additional case of a retroperitoneal bronchogenic cyst that presented uniquely as a symptomatic adrenal mass and discuss the cases of subdiaphragmatic bronchogenic cysts reported in the English-language literature.
